I"‰<p>This will send a message when someone in your known devices list connects to your local network. In other words, when someone arrives home. It will only work if you are using the <a href="/integrations/nmap_tracker">Nmap</a> device tracker or a similar integration.</p>
<p>This example uses <a href="/integrations/telegram">Telegram</a> to send the notification.</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">notify:
  - name: Telegram
    platform: telegram
    api_key: xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
    chat_id: xxxxxxxxx
</code></pre>
<p>Add the automation rule. Change <code>device_name_here</code> to match the device you want to track.</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml">automation:
  trigger:
    platform: state
    entity_id: device_tracker.device_name_here
    from: 'not_home'
    to: 'home'
  action:
    service: notify.Telegram
    data:
      message: 'Person is now home'
</code></pre>
